column1: This table is field data collected in the upper reaches of the Blue Duck Creek in the foothills of the Seaward Kaikoura Range, New Zealand.
This data set was created by Eric Barefoot and Emily Beckham by hiking along streams and taking wetted stream width measurements every ~5 meters with a tape measure.
This data was collected to determine the distribution of stream widths in headwater catchments.
GPS waypoints were taken at nodes in the stream network.

column2: We either paced upstream or downstream
Raw width measurements taken in inches
Estimated percentage of the streams that were not flowing due to sandbars, rocks, vegetation, or other material at the surface of the stream

column3: divine measurement - width visually estimated (only done a few times in blue duck where ongaonga was too dense to measure)

width measured using a long tape measure - width in cm
